news.title: Edelweiss Securities leases 1 lakh sq ft in Adani Realty's office tower in Mumbai
news.para: The firm is expected to pay total rentals worth over Rs 285 crore over the tenure of the lease based on monthly rentals of Rs 220 per sq ft, including common area maintenance charges.

news.title: Punjab to use GPS tracking, bar code scanners to check illegal sand mining: Report
news.para: The recommendations include use of digital technology such as remote sensing data in order to scientifically determine the extent of legal and illegal sand mining in and around the operational sand mining sites in the state.

news.title: Chandigarh: Extra FAR charges likely to be based on type of properties
news.para: The UT administration is going to adopt different formula for calculating charges for different types of properties in connection with availing additional floor area ratio (FAR). In the coming days, the UT will also form a sub-committee in this regard.

news.title: Not a single taker for 25 freehold properties of Chandigarh housing board
news.para: The board had invited bids for the sale of 25 built-up properties, including 23 residential and two commercial, on freehold basis.

news.title: Rajasthan: Prashasan campaign picks up pace, more pattas being issued
news.para: At the Jaipur Development Authority, which is considered as biggest civic body in the state, the administration has issued 5,500 Pattas in last 10 days.

news.title: Chandigarh: 50% property tax waiver for EWS houses
news.para: Approval was also given to waive off 100% penalty amount of three financial years of 2019-2020, 2020-2021 and 2021-2022 of the EWS houses.

news.title: Raze illegal buildings obstructing flights where there's no stay: Bombay HC
news.para: Mumbai International Airport Ltd had in its July 8 reply given details of obstacle surveys carried out by it over the years.

news.title: Gurugram: Two years on, AVL 36 residents yet to get an elected RWA
news.para: The residents have complained that the developer had registered an apartment owners association in March 2020 and nominated its close aides as the office bearers of the association without holding any election process.

news.title: FIR against Supertech, maintenance agency after woman suffers injury in lift
news.para: ​In a complaint to the police, the woman's son alleged the lift had a "free fall" when the incident took place on July 19 and this was not the first time that they faced such maintenance issue in the Supertech Supernova society in Sector 94.

news.title: Gurugram: Seven illegal colonies razed in DTCP drive in five days
news.para: In the last five days, the department has freed more than 37 acres of prime agricultural land in the city by razing around 120 under construction buildings and offices in 7 illegal colonies.

news.title: Nagpur: Consumer court awards 24 years jail to builder for contempt
news.para: ​The builder — Revathi Associate and Infrastructure Limited’s owner Suhas Morey – was convicted for 3 years each for contempt in total eight cases.

news.title: CBI files charge sheet against builder Avinash Bhosale in Yes Bank-DHFL scam
news.para: The agency has also named Satyan Gopaldas Tandon, Metropolis Hotels LLP, ABIL Infraprojects Pvt Ltd, ABIL Hospitality Pvt Ltd, Arindam Developers, Avinash Bhosale Group and Flora Developments Ltd in connection with the case in its supplementary charge sheet filed before a special CBI court in Mumbai.

news.title: SC stays arbitral proceedings between Dhoni & Amrapali group over commercial dispute
news.para: ​The apex court-appointed forensic auditors had told the bench that Amrapali Group had entered into "sham agreements" with Rhiti Sports Management which promotes the brand of Dhoni, to "illegally divert" home buyers' money and a total amount of Rs 42.22 crore was paid to RSMPL during 2009-2015.

news.title: UP RERA allows more time to promoter to complete covid-hit project in Ghaziabad
news.para: ​The RERA noted that work on Utopia Estate commenced in April 2016 but could not be completed by promoter M/s Sai Adhiraj Land & Promoters Pvt Ltd within the stipulated time which ended on March 28, 2022, according to an official statement.

news.title: Kamdhenu's net profit dips 11% in Q1 FY23
news.para: Kamdhenu's total consolidated income stood at Rs 191.27 crore in Q1 FY23, a growth of 68.33 per cent from Rs 113.63 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.
